### ===================================================
### 3. PRUEBAS DE SEGURIDAD (Debe fallar sin token)
### ===================================================

### Listar órdenes sin token (Debe responder 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/orders

###

### Listar productos en Inventory sin token (Debe responder 401 Unauthorized)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/products

###

### ===================================================
### 4. INVENTORY SERVICE (Vía API Gateway con JWT)
### ===================================================

### Obtener todos los productos
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/products
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### Obtener producto por ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/products/1
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### Crear producto (Esto también disparará el evento ProductCreatedEvent)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "Teclado Mecánico RGB",
  "quantity": 11,
  "price": 99.99
}

###

### ===================================================
### 5. ORDER SERVICE (Vía API Gateway con JWT)
### ===================================================

### Crear una orden (Dispara evento OrderCreatedEvent)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "productName": "Mouse Inalámbrico Pro",
  "quantity": 2,
  "price": 85.0
}

###

### Listar todas las órdenes (Debe mostrar la orden recién creada)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/orders
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### Obtener orden por ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/orders/1
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### ===================================================
### 6. PRUEBAS DE ACCESO DIRECTO (Sin pasar por API Gateway)
### ===================================================

### Obtener todos los productos (directo a inventory-service)
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/api/inventory/products
Authorization: {{token}}

###

### Crear producto (directo a inventory-service)
POST {{inventoryUrl}}/api/inventory/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "Producto Directo",
  "quantity": 5,
  "price": 49.99
}

###

### ===================================================
### 7. VERIFICACIÓN DE FLUJO DE EVENTOS (INTEGRACIÓN)
### ===================================================

### Simular creación de producto para verificar flujo:
# Al ejecutar esta petición:
# 1. inventory-service publica un evento "ProductCreated" en Kafka/RabbitMQ.
# 2. order-service consume el evento y registra en sus logs la recepción.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/inventory/products
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "name": "Monitor Gamer 144Hz",
  "quantity": 10,
  "price": 299.99
}

###

### Simular creación de orden para verificar flujo:
# Al ejecutar esta petición:
# 1. order-service publica un evento "OrderCreated" en Kafka/RabbitMQ.
# 2. notification-service consume el evento y emite logs de notificación.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/orders
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: {{token}}

{
  "productName": "Auriculares HyperX",
  "quantity": 1,
  "price": 75.0
}

###

### ===================================================
### 8. MONITOREO, HEALTH CHECKS & ACTUATOR
### ===================================================

### Eureka Health
GET http://localhost:8761/actuator/health

###

### Config Server Health
GET http://localhost:8888/actuator/health

###

### Inventory Service Health
GET {{inventoryUrl}}/actuator/health

###

### Order Service Health (Directo)
GET {{orderUrl}}/actuator/health

###

### Order Service Health (Vía Gateway)
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/actuator/health

###

### H2 Console (Información)
# H2 Console (inventory-service): http://localhost:8082/h2-console
# JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:inventorydb | User: sa | Password: (vacío)
#
# H2 Console (order-service): http://localhost:8085/h2-console
# JDBC URL: jdbc:h2:mem:orderdb | User: sa | Password: (vacío)
